CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 28, 1957, pg. 2, reads: "Gutted School - Firemen 'water down' Elementary School One before a wrecking crew knocked down the masonry walls which were weakened by the disastrous Rankin fire. Besides school books, a $30,000 new medical and dental laboratory in school was destroyed. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Fire fighters spraying water on burning Elementary School One, Rankin
